The paper focuses on automated common-sense inference, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a framework for extracting common-sense knowledge and uses a sequence to sequence neural network model for training and evaluation, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of previously established datasets, which could fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
